article.headline: Akron 64, Duquesne 61 (OT)
article.story: AKRON, Ohio (AP) -- Derrick Tarver had 18 points, including six in overtime, to lead Akron over Duquesne 64-61 Wednesday night. Duquesne (2-4) trailed by as many as 10 in the second half but tied it at 55 on Martin Osimani's jumper with 1:03 left. Ryan Tricco hit a 3-pointer to put Duquesne up with 3:45 left in overtime, but Akron clamped down on defense and allowed just six points in the extra period. Tarver had two fast-break layups in the final minute of overtime to put Akron (4-2) on top for good. Bryant McAllister led Duquesne with 21 points, Jimmy Tricco had 16 and Elijah Palmer had 15 points and 11 rebounds. Romeo Travis had 12 points and 14 rebounds off the bench for Akron. The Zips won despite shooting only 32 percent from the field and 55 percent from the free throw line.
